pageContext.claim: “There's been no collusion whatsoever. There’s no obstruction whatsoever. And I'm looking forward to [speaking with Mueller]. I do worry when I look at all of the things that you people don't report about, with what's happening.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump repeatedly claims the Russia investigation is made up or "Democratic-inspired," but the information on Russian efforts to sway the 2016 election was developed by the intelligence community and published in a declassified report, in which the agencies said they had "high confidence" it was correct. Whether or not there was collusion is still under investigation. His lawyers quickly walked back the president's eagerness to meet with Special Counsel Robert Mueller.
